Class ModelWorkFactory<T>

java.lang.Object
org.nasdanika.emf.ModelWorkFactory<T>
All Implemented Interfaces:
BiFunction<Context,ProgressMonitor,T>, ContextualFactory<Supplier<T>>, ExecutionParticipantFactory<Supplier<T>>, Factory<Context,Supplier<T>>, SupplierFactory<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
ValidatingModelWorkFactory
public class ModelWorkFactory<T> extends Object implements SupplierFactory<T>
This class loads a model with the root element, adapts it to SupplierFactory, and delegates its methods to it.

  • Method Details

    • createResourceSet

      public static org.eclipse.emf.ecore.resource.ResourceSet createResourceSet(org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EPackage... ePackages)
      Creates a new ResourceSet if it was not passed to a constructor explicitly. This implementation creates a new resource set and configures it to load the model by registering an XMIResourceFactoryImpl and putting NcorePackage to the package registry. If the model uses model elements from other EPackages pass a resource set constructed by the client to one of the constructors which accept resource set. The resource set can be constructed by this method and then additional packages may be registered by the client code before passing the resource set to a constructor.
